caption: The best oxtail empanadas in NYC!!!!

I really liked this place. It's small and a little intimate so great for a date night. The food is amazing! Had the oxtail empanadas, the jerk chicken mac & cheese, and beef sliders. Everything was delicious. Found a new favorite drink: mango ginger margarita. Can't wait to go back.  *FYI - they add a 20% gratuity and a covid-19 charge to your bill.

My husband and I were visiting New York for the weekend. I found this restaurant online on the night of 2/27/21. I called the number to ask about seating. The person who answered the phone, Alex, was amazing. He took his time explaining the covid procedures, the seating and the parking. We felt welcome before we got there. Our waiter Sky was just as nice. The food was amazing. We had the shrimp appetizer and jerk Mac and cheese. Absolutely delicious! Great food and great service. Alex assured us that even though the parking was a bit sketchy, we would be ok and we were. He checked on us a few times to reassure our comfort.

Absolutely amazing. If you are looking for a place that gives off that southern homey vibe,  this is definitely the place. Always a good time!  Food is fabulous!

Lovely space with a good vibe and amazing food. Small restaurant with an intimate feeling. I think this place is perfect for a date night. The food truely blew my mind. We had the jerk chicken Mac and cheese which was spot on and could be a stand alone entree if u ask me. Then I have the steak with mash potatoes be and kale which was so good I took my time to enjoy every bite. My date short ribs with mash potatoes and greens which was so tender he didn't even need a knife. To cap the meal we had a fabulous red sangria that I can't wait to have again. This will definitely be my new it spot in harlem.

Low key sexy lounge/bar. Sunday brunch til 7pm. Bartender Lola is amazing. I had the chicken and waffles which was okay. The chicken isn't your typical fried chicken. It doesn't taste like it has flouring on it. My date had the shrimp and grits which was delicious. The dj played a good variety of music. It was a nice atmosphere for adults, I'll definitely be back.

Cute little place in Harlem. The food was good and the staff was nice. The place is a little small, so make sure you make reservations.

My first time going and regret it. Feel like I wasted my money. The bartender made me and my friend watered down drinks for $15 which I ended up making my own drink with the help of my waitress and courtesy of the owner. The bartender was very unprofessional. Talking loud, very unhelpful, rude to her coworker in front of customers and the loud convo between her and other customers was a turn off, pertaining to fighting and biting people. This is not what i want to hear during dinner and cocktails trying to enjoy my night. Her aura and unprofessionalism made us leave with our food and not want to stay. Definitely not what we expected and will not be returning. If one employee can turn away customers then you know something is wrong.

The service was excellent- Angelica was the best waitress. This place is definately a Gem. I hound this place by chance. The food was amazing and the drinks were very well prepared. You have to stop by, tell them Pat- Karizma sent you. Lamb chops and shrimp were the absolute best.

Loved ALL of the food; especially the shrimp and shaved kale salad. Oh and the Red Sangria is CRAZY!!!! Can't wait to host an event here. Love seeing a Black People doing their thing. Congrats! Harlem has a new hot spot.

Organic everything from the Wine to the chicken,  thats what i was told.  The Asian chicken wings,  sweet, spicy and crunchy.  I'm in love with those chicken wings.  They can keep the jerk mac&cheese,  i didn't like that.  The bartender name Lola is a Boss,  she broke down everything....she explained about the organic wines etc, she was very friendly and detail. Its a new and different local  Restaurant lounge....i don't think there is a place that is offering Organic wines/alcohol and food in Harlem. Only con....its very small in side and the kitchen doesn't open until 5, best that .This restaurant is a must try.

WoW! Went here today for brunch. The ambiance, service and food all deserve 5 Stars. Glad to see establishments like this in Harlem. I enjoyed a Bellini and fresh fruit red sangria while Michael Jackson blared from the speakers. I ordered the brunch burrito and couldn’t refrain from also ordering the Jerk Mac N Cheese. Both were extremely favorable and seasoned to perfection. The menu has tons of options and they were very attentive to my shellfish allergy. If you’re ever uptown and in search of a delicious meal with great service or even just drinks...... we can’t forget the drinks! Stop by and check it out.
Went there to watch the Superbowl.. small, modern and cozy, chill clientele, the staff is nice, tasty food and original menu (had the cauliflower steak), reasonably priced for being NY.. just great !

I've been to this restaurant a few time since the very recent Grand Opening and I have to say both the food and the drinks are AMAZING! ?The bartenders are very friendly and welcoming and the waitresses are on point!  The ambiance is grown and sexy and the music is Great.

The wait staff here was on point with making sure I was taken care of. So many signature drinks to choose from and the 2 I had were amazing. Owner was present and greeted our table and was really friendly. This is the new spot for a good vibe in Harlem
